# placeholders.manifest — the DECLARED set of install-time placeholders.
#
# The installer (bootstrap/hos_install.sh) substitutes {NAME} in
# .claude/agents/*.md from the matching NAME in scripts/framework/config.sh
# (env override wins). This file is the single source of truth for WHICH tokens
# are install-time placeholders — it must be declared, not guessed, because
# agent prompts also contain runtime tokens ({N}, {HEAD_SHA}, {BASE_SHA}, JSON
# examples like {role}) that must NOT be substituted.
#
# When you introduce a new {PLACEHOLDER} into an agent template, add ONE line
# here. On the next install/upgrade the installer will:
#   - append the new key to each project's config.sh (empty, non-destructive —
#     existing values are never touched), and
#   - leave the {NAME} token in place (not blanked) until a value is set,
#     with a warning naming the unset keys.
#
# Format:  NAME<TAB>description / example
PROJECT_NAME	Human-readable project name used in agent prompts (e.g. CondoParkShare)
SPEC_FILE	Path to the primary spec file, repo-relative (e.g. Specs/SPEC-1-pilot.md)
DESIGN_PACK_DIR	Directory holding the design pack (e.g. docs/design)
ADR_FILE	Path to the architect's ADR — architectural decisions / boundaries (e.g. docs/architecture/ADR-001.md)
